    <!-- About Section -->
    <section id="about">
        <h3>About Us</h3>
        <p>
            Access to safe, reliable, and affordable transportation remains a persistent challenge in Lesotho, 
            especially in urban centers like Maseru and remote rural areas. Public transport options are often 
            inconsistent, informal, and lack digital integration, leaving passengers with limited choices and 
            unpredictable travel experiences.
        </p>
        <p>
            Catch-a-Ride is designed to transform how people move around Lesotho. We offer a dependable, 
            transparent, and user-friendly ride-hailing service that not only addresses transportation inefficiencies 
            but also creates new economic opportunities for drivers and small fleet owners.
        </p>
        <p>
            Our commitment is to the Basotho communities ‚Äî providing a service that prioritizes safety, 
            convenience, and affordability, while also contributing to a more sustainable urban environment.
        </p>
    </section>

    <!-- How It Works Section -->
    <section id="how-it-works">
        <h3>How It Works</h3>

        <div class="how-container">

            <!-- For Riders -->
            <div class="how-group">
                <h4>For Riders</h4>

                <div class="step">
                    <h5>1. Request a Ride</h5>
                    <p>Download the Catch-a-Ride app (or use our SMS service for basic booking). Enter your destination and request a ride or parcel delivery instantly.</p>
                </div>

                <div class="step">
                    <h5>2. Track & Travel</h5>
                    <p>Track your driver‚Äôs arrival in real-time. Enjoy a safe, comfortable, and efficient journey to your destination or watch your parcel reach its recipient.</p>
                </div>

                <div class="step">
                    <h5>3. Pay & Rate</h5>
                    <p>Pay securely through the app. After your trip, rate your driver and provide feedback to help us maintain high-quality service.</p>
                </div>
            </div>

            <!-- For Drivers -->
            <div class="how-group">
                <h4>For Drivers</h4>

                <div class="step">
                    <h5>1. Sign Up & Go Online</h5>
                    <p>Register as a Catch-a-Ride driver. Once approved, simply go online in the app to start receiving ride or parcel delivery requests.</p>
                </div>

                <div class="step">
                    <h5>2. Accept & Navigate</h5>
                    <p>Accept nearby requests. Our smart routing guides you to your passenger or parcel and then efficiently to their destination.</p>
                </div>

                <div class="step">
                    <h5>3. Earn & Grow</h5>
                    <p>Complete trips and deliveries, earning income with every successful journey. Grow your business with a reliable platform.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Impact Section -->
    <section id="impact">
        <h3>Our Impact</h3>
        <p>
            Catch-a-Ride is more than just a transportation app; it's a catalyst for positive change in Lesotho. 
            By promoting shared mobility, we actively contribute to reducing traffic congestion and lowering 
            greenhouse gas emissions, fostering cleaner urban environments.
        </p>
        <p>
            We're committed to providing accessible and affordable transport solutions, bridging the gap between 
            urban centres and rural communities. This not only enhances user satisfaction but also empowers local 
            individuals by creating vital economic opportunities for drivers and small fleet owners, strengthening 
            the local economy.
        </p>
        <p>
            Our vision is to build a sustainable and thriving mobility ecosystem that serves the unique needs of 
            Basotho, ensuring everyone has access to safe, reliable, and respectful transportation.
        </p>
    </section>

    <!-- For Drivers Section -->
    <section id="drivers">
